{
  "texts": [
    "Conventional manufacturing practices frequently compromise the nutritional quality of food products, while insufficient traceability in the food supply chain raises concerns over safety and nutritional reliability (3).",
    "These dual challenges, generic dietary guidance and inefficient food production systems, necessitate a paradigm shift driven by technological innovation.",
    "Artificial intelligence (AI) has emerged as a transformative enabler in this context.",
    "Through advanced techniques such as machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), AI facilitates the extraction of actionable insights from complex health and dietary datasets (4, 5).",
    "AI-powered systems are increasingly capable of delivering real-time, individualized dietary recommendations, especially for chronic disease management."
  ]
}